structures.label: Bernard of Clairvaux OCist, De gratia et libero arbitrio

description: This twelfth- or thirteenth-century manuscript, written in a beautiful hand, contains miscellaneous learned theological texts, including Bernard of Clairvaux OCist (1090-1153), De gratia et libero arbitrio, the abridgement of the Sentences of Peter Lombard (c. 1095-1160) by Gandulf of Bologna (d. after 1185), the Expositio missae which is part of the De diuinis officiis of Remigius of Auxerre (d. 908), and an unidentified text De poenitentia. The manuscript also contains a copy of the letters of Arnulf of Lisieux (d. 1184) who was bishop of Lisieux 1141-81.
